 will manifest.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nI'm a mom - I'm lucky if I get to shower in the morning. Luckily, nail polish stays on my toes. I've been so bad on the upkeep, though.\n\n- Idina\n|\nMen like you and I make myths, we weave stories to sanctify the life that has been given to us. But not Govinda. Men like him don’t make myths; they make destiny. – Kshatta Vidur\n\n- Krishna Udayasankar, Kurukshetra\n|\nBe a control freak and people will avoid you. Live and let live, and people will get closer to you and do the same for you.\n\n- Innocent Mwatsikesimbe, Mirror\n|\nA little while, their hunger unfulfilled,The mothlike worlds flit 'round the guttering sun.('Ephemera')\n\n- George Sterling, The Thirst of Satan: Poems of Fantasy and Terror\n|\nI really liked 'Blk Girl Art.' It's like a manifesto saying why I create, whether it's poetry or music.\n\n- Jamila\n|\nAlways write to change society for the better. You will go, but it will live forever as a treasure.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nI don't need time, I need a deadline.\n\n- Duke\n|\nYou are happy when you are enthusiastic and action-oriented, not when you are luxury and pleasure oriented.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nAh, summer, what power you have to make us suffer and like it.\n\n- Russell\n|\nTo me you were home, to you I was just a vacation.\n\n- Sade Andria Zabala, Coffee and Cigarettes\n|\nHave you ever considered that you shouldn't pray for God to deliver you from your enemies, rather deliver you from yourself so you can not hate them?\n\n- Shannon\n|\nIf you lose the power to love, you lose the ability to live.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nFor those who trust, life is a blessing. For those who don't trust, life is suffering.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nStop worrying about what tomorrow brings, God is already preparing some amazing things way ahead of you.\n\n- Unknown\n|\nPart-time effort, won't yield full-time results\n\n- S.B.\n|\nAlways good to remember when you're making art. You don't have to like it, just be ready to do the next thing.\n\n- Neil\n|\nA few steps into the trees, you glance back to see the snow has already covered your prints.\n\n- Jennifer\n|\nTo dance is to be out of yourself. Larger, more beautiful, more powerful. This is power, it is glory on earth and it is yours for the taking.\n\n- Agnes\n|\nA novel, though fiction, often speaks to the largest truths.\n\n- Mark\n|\nWhen two warring people face each other, the war of words jumps beyond the subject. The subject remains no more central to the arguments.\n\n- Girdhar Joshi, Some Mistakes Have No Pardon\n|\nBy nature man without woman can feel no joy. She is his mother, his sister, his loving friend. She is seldom his enemy.\n\n- Christine\n|\nA rich man, was one who spent a million.\n\n- Brian McGreevy, Hemlock Grove\n|\nIf I let a little of the emotion out, all of it will come out, and it will never end.\n\n- Veronica Roth, Allegiant\n|\nAfter living out of a suitcase for years, it's a feeling of peace to wake up in the night and know where I am.\n\n- Patty\n|\nWhen you are dealing with an invisible enemy,use most resources as shield, and a bit as a bait.\n\n- Toba Beta, Betelgeuse Incident: Insiden Bait Al-Jauza\n|\nWhile God desires salvation for everyone, God owes salvation to no one.\n\n- Evan Minton, A Hellacious Doctrine: A Defense Of The Biblical Doctrine Of Hell\n|\nWhenever you smile, whenever you care, whenever you love, whenever you share, your spirit will dance with joy because happiness is there.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nComplexity is a product of unawareness and simplicity a result of awareness! Uncomplex yourself, Live Life!\n\n- Ramana\n|\nAn eye for an eye will only make the world bright. Sorry, Mahatma. This is the absolute and only true form of justice.\n\n- Natalya\n|\n…you either do or do not have a comedy mind, whatever that is, maybe a heightened sense of the ridiculous and the absurdity of life…We are all crazy and crazed.\n\n- Joan Rivers, Enter Talking\n|\nWithout failure, there is no success.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nBashfulness is an ornament to youth, but a reproach to old age.\n\n- Aristotle\n|\nFire looked into his quiet eyes, touched his dear familiar face and considered the question.\n\n- Kristin Cashore, Fire\n|\nSo many things in my continuing education are learned by going where I have to go and doing what I have to do. Therefore, my only answer is: 'I guess I'll find out.\n\n- Dean Koontz, Odd Interlude: A Special Odd Thomas Adventure\n|\nI really, sincerely believe that one should trust the work, and not the author.\n\n- Peter\n|\nAll men are created equal, it is only men themselves who place themselves above equality.\n\n- David\n|\nBlaming others for your mistakes, makes you powerless to change your life. Taking responsibility for your mistakes, gives you the power to change your life\n\n- Karon\n|\nIf you sent speaking pages, they would be like a brother to me.\n\n- Radegund\n|\nI'm not letting the world - or anyone in it - determine my fate. Not anymore, at least. - Ginny\n\n- Jackson Pearce, Cold Spell\n|\nI hear some people say, 'I wish I could rewind time.' But why rewind time, when every single day brings a great opportunity to start a wonderful new beginning?\n\n- Unknown\n|\nStrangers will show you the wayBut a true friend will escort you,to your destination.1st November, 2006\n\n- Tushar\n|\nWhen you experience permanent bliss of the Self (samadhi), then it will be considered that your entire work is completed.\n\n- Dada\n|\nPart of the $10 million I spent on gambling, part on booze and part on women. The rest I spent foolishly.\n\n- George\n|\nHe who defends with love will be secure; Heaven will save him, and protect him with love.\n\n- Lao\n|\nA positive attitude turns 'I can't & I won't,' into 'I have & I WILL!\n\n- Mandy Hale, The Single Woman: Life, Love, and a Dash of Sass\n|\nChildren of the same family, the same blood, with the same first associations and habits, have some means of enjoyment in theirpower, which no subsequent connections can supply..\n\n- Jane Austen, Mansfield Park\n|\nIf a man's character is to be abused, say what you will, there's nobody like a relative to do the business.\n\n- William Makepeace Thackeray, Vanity Fair\n|\nLord, grant that I may always desire more than I can accomplish.\n\n- Michelangelo\n|\nIf your business still needs to change, isn’t it likely that your thinking needs to change first?\n\n- A.J.  Sheppard, The Incredible Transformation of Gregory Todd\n|\nIt was always the secrets that hurt us, wasn't it? Not the telling of them.\n\n- Betsy Cornwell, Tides\n|\nGenius is when you strike a chord accidently, and the ensuing music is beyond your control\n\n- Bangambiki Habyarimana, The Great Pearl of Wisdom\n|\nNot sorry, not calling, not cryingAll will pass like smoke of white apple treesSeized by the gold of autumn,I will no longer be young.\n\n- Sergei\n|\nThat's what we all want, isn't it? Power without price.\n\n- Kelley Armstrong, The Summoning\n|\nA year from today, it will be Good if your life is positively different, but GREAT if your life has made a positive difference on others\n\n- Fela\n|\nGod doesn't act like the Church. No, instead, the Church must act like God.\n\n- Kim\n|\nHe tries to force the anger down, but it's like an anvil on his chest. He closes his eyes, like Sammy taught him, and forces the anvil up; he softens.\n\n- Chris Crutcher, The Crazy Horse Electric Game\n|\nThose with calling also find wealth, so jump and start swimming towards your true self.\n\n- Ryan\n|\nThe inspired words, which flush my mind, come from a higher power!\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Think Great: Be Great!\n|\nAt the end of the day, all you can hope for is to go on. The older I get, the more I realize that just keeping on keeping on is what life's all about.\n\n- Janis\n|\nLove consists of not looking each other in the eye, but of looking outwardly in the same direction.\n\n- Antoine de Saint-Exupéry, Airman's Odyssey\n|\nYuvraj Singh is one of the best batsmen to watch in world cricket