ppy.\n\n- Richelle E. Goodrich, Making Wishes\n|\nLiving is a process of developing oneself. Without experiencing pain from disconcerting periods of our lives, we would be different person, perhaps a lesser person.\n\n- Kilroy J. Oldster, Dead Toad Scrolls\n|\nDon't get caught in 'Waiting'. When I 'Get This' then I will be able to fully 'Live'. Escape the time dominant mind by fully being here 'NOW'.\n\n- Matthew\n|\nThe bitterest hardships, the most daunting trials; none of these are burdens if it means being with you.\n\n- Richelle E. Goodrich, Smile Anyway\n|\nThe really essential factors of success in any undertaking are money and opportunity, and as a rule, the man who can make the first can make the second.\n\n- Dorothy L. Sayers, Whose Body?\n|\nI'm often dating people, but I don't say it because you sort of know it won't last long.\n\n- Graham\n|\nYou have no idea how dearly I wish you were of my blood. My daughter, granddaughter. Will you allow me to take pride in what you are?'-- Sandre to Catriana\n\n- Guy Gavriel Kay, Tigana\n|\nWe make our own luck. I believed that, too. We chose our own fate. We controlled our own future. I knew what I wanted. I needed to go get it.\n\n- Kasie West, Lucky in Love\n|\n...I remember the oily smoke of a cigarette suspended in a shaft of sunlight - with you, everything was beautiful...\n\n- John\n|\nSavings, remember, is the prerequisite of investment.\n\n- Campbell R. McConnell, Economics\n|\nDon't wish,'said Rain, 'don't start. Wishing only...\n\n- Gregory Maguire, Out of Oz\n|\nI have to know, I have to or else you will just rule me until the end of everything because you know and I do not.\n\n- Catherynne M. Valente, Deathless"